==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carronade
<hw>Car`ron*ade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Carron</ets>, in Scotland where it was first made.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of short cannon, formerly in use, designed
to throw a large projectile with small velocity, used for the purpose of
breaking or smashing in, rather than piercing, the object aimed at, as
the side of a ship. It has no trunnions, but is supported on its
carriage by a bolt passing through a loop on its under side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 221 --></p>

<p><ent>Carron oil</ent>⟦br⟧
